&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Step into a career with ASM, where cutting edge technology meets collaborative culture. &lt;/strong&gt;​&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For over 55 years ASM has been ahead of what’s next, at the forefront of innovation and what’s technologically possible. With more than 4,500 ASMers representing 70 nationalities, our people and our advanced semiconductor devices are playing a crucial role in trends such as 5G, cloud computing, AI, and autonomous driving.  But&amp;nbsp;we’re more than just a tech company. We value diversity, inclusion and sustainability as we strive to make a positive impact on the world.&amp;nbsp; Our development programs help support your growth, shaping your future and pushing the boundaries of innovation to unleash potential.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Duties &amp;amp; Responsibilities:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Finance Business Partner to Core Corporate Functions such as Corporate Business Development, Risk Management, Tax, Government Relations and Environmental, Health &amp;amp; Safety teams&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monthly financial controlling, compliance with internal controls and analysis for responsible corporate functions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Month end closing activities of responsible corporate functions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monthly forecasting and annual budgeting of responsible corporate functions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist and support for monthly corporate and group reporting&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist and support for annual budgeting exercise&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive cost and efficiency improvements of responsible corporate functions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support implementation of financial projects for responsible corporate functions and other projects for corporate reporting such as new platform implementation and M&amp;amp;A integrations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Required Experience &amp;amp; Skills:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Self-motivated and results oriented with a strong business acumen&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven success in preparing financial forecasts and budgets; able to prioritize when meeting deadlines&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Hands-on, proactive, meticulous with keen attention to details&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong analytical, problem solving, and organizational skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Good communication skills along with the confidence to excel in an ambiguous environment with a flexible mindset approach&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven ability to influence and collaborate with executive audiences&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Deep understanding of accounting principles and best financial practices&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proficiency with SAP or other fully integrated ERP systems&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong knowledge of Excel and Microsoft Office&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience working in a global, matrixed reporting organization&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Education &amp;amp; Qualifications&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelor’s or Master’s degree in Accounting or Finance; MBA or CPA preferred&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;5 – 10 years of relevant experience, ideally in semiconductor or high-tech manufacturing with minimum 3 years of experience in the FP&amp;amp;A field, combined with other business/finance control roles and/or Big4 background&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;content-conclusion&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Apply today to be part of what’s next.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We make the tech that enables the chips in devices which improve lives around the world. We do this with an eye to the future, pushing the boundaries of what’s possible through cutting-edge innovation, and driving the next wave of technological breakthroughs that shape how we live, work, and connect.&lt;/p&gt;
