&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Step into a career with ASM, where cutting edge technology meets collaborative culture. &lt;/strong&gt;​&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For over 55 years ASM has been ahead of what’s next, at the forefront of innovation and what’s technologically possible. With more than 4,500 ASMers representing 70 nationalities, our people and our advanced semiconductor devices are playing a crucial role in trends such as 5G, cloud computing, AI, and autonomous driving.  But&amp;nbsp;we’re more than just a tech company. We value diversity, inclusion and sustainability as we strive to make a positive impact on the world.&amp;nbsp; Our development programs help support your growth, shaping your future and pushing the boundaries of innovation to unleash potential.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;About the role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a Device, Fabrication &amp;amp; Test Manager at ASM, you will directly shape the development and integration of next-generation semiconductor technologies. In this unique role, you will drive how we design, fabricate and evaluate electrical test structures that underpin the performance of our ALD and advanced materials portfolio - impacting both logic and memory applications. You’ll operate at the intersection of device physics, process integration and data-driven innovation, partnering closely with product teams to accelerate development cycles and enable breakthrough performance.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you’ll do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead and scale a high-performing engineering team focused on fabrication and electrical characterization of advanced test structures (MOS, MIM, FETs)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Translate complex electrical data into actionable insights (CV, IV, Dit) to guide process development and integration of ASM technologies such as ALD films&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive innovation in testing capabilities, from fabrication processes and measurement techniques to data collection, automation and analytics&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Shape future test strategies by designing novel test structures and methodologies aligned with evolving product requirements&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own project prioritization and execution, balancing multiple high-impact initiatives across stakeholders&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Mentor and develop engineers, building deep expertise in device physics, fabrication, testing and data analysis&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you bring&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Master’s or Ph.D. in Electrical Engineering, Physics, Materials Science or related field&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong industry experience in semiconductor device fabrication, testing and analysis&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven leadership experience (people management or technical leadership)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Hands-on experience with programming/scripting (Python preferred)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Your strengths&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Deep expertise in device physics, semiconductor technology and process integration&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong hands-on experience in layout design, cleanroom fabrication and process flows&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Solid background in electrical testing, data analysis and interpretation of device behavior&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to leverage data at scale - automation, scripting and efficient analysis&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong prioritization skills in a dynamic, fast-paced R&amp;amp;D environment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Effective collaborator, able to influence across multidisciplinary teams&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Clear communicator, able to translate complex technical concepts to diverse audiences&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
